    "body": "vyper is on `conda-forge` now. You can install it by following instructions at https://github.com/conda-forge/vyper-feedstock (although you may want to wait for the 0.2.11 release as 0.2.10 has a major bug ;))\r\n\r\n```\r\nconda search vyper --info\r\nLoading channels: done\r\nvyper 0.2.10 pyhd8ed1ab_0\r\n-------------------------\r\nfile name   : vyper-0.2.10-pyhd8ed1ab_0.tar.bz2\r\nname        : vyper\r\nversion     : 0.2.10\r\nbuild       : pyhd8ed1ab_0\r\nbuild number: 0\r\nsize        : 132 KB\r\nlicense     : Apache-2.0\r\nsubdir      : noarch\r\nurl         : https://conda.anaconda.org/conda-forge/noarch/vyper-0.2.10-pyhd8ed1ab_0.tar.bz2\r\nmd5         : 8f14920e1d20c5ebe46c23fd189a7302\r\ntimestamp   : 2021-02-22 17:54:53 UTC\r\ndependencies: \r\n  - asttokens 2.0.4\r\n  - pycryptodome >=3.5.1,<4\r\n  - python >=3.6\r\n  - semantic_version 2.8.5\r\n```",
